1) I have seen the GNU license before on the linux website.

2) This license is saying that this is a free software that you can redistribute it ot modify it freely

3)The implications this license has for the author is that it will be used without warranty and will be free .For the user the implications are that they will not intend to put a warranty on it 

4)You would use this license to allow people to modify, share, and study the program in order to make it useful to them but without the intent of adding any warantees

5)You would not use this license if you wanted people to pay to use this program
